  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 36bccf2d2c1763242ba11eb36cdffde2, type: 3}
  m_Name: NewspaperBook
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  pages:
  - text: 'July 15, 2009


      Arkansas to Become a Desert?


      Scientists
      warn that if climate change continues unchecked, Arkansas could resemble the
      deserts of Nevada by the year 2100. Forests and farmland may give way to vast
      sandy plains, while prolonged droughts leave only cacti and other heat-resistant
      plants able to survive. Though the prediction may seem unbelievable today,
      researchers insist it could become reality without decisive action.'
  actions: []
